body:
@ncw This is brilliant. It worked perfectly for me!
I am sorry I ended up not having time enough to contribute to the project.
I hope I will be able to do so in the future.

@pedrosimao thanks for testing

>  I have one comment though. I have tried to run the "moveto" command to copy a Folder from Gdrive (scope "drive", accessible via web interface) to a Folder inside "drive.appfolder" scope. And it seems rclone downloads the entire content to my computer and later copy it to the appfolder, unlike it does while moving from inside the same scope, where folder is simply renamed. Do you think it is possible to only use the "rename" strategy, instead of copying it all over again?

I don't know whether Google let you do this.  A bit of experimenting makes me beleive that it isn't possible.  You certainly can't do it with rclone because you need to have a remote which shows both the contents of the appdata folder and the files in drive and that isn't possible with the current drive APIs.  I suspect even if you did manage to do it somehow, the files wouldn't be readable by rclone as they would have the wrong permissions.
